          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can customize the window tab by adding an accessory view that displays alongside the tab’s title."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1526961-translatesautoresizingmaskintoco"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property is automatically set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " on the view. Constraints can be created and activated to specify the view’s width and height values. A constraint is automatically added to vertically center the view, and to right align the view within the tab."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
